<TITLE> Construction worker dies, 3 more injured </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, May 5 (bdnews24.com)A building construction worker was killed and four more injured as a roof of a house under construction collapsed. The incident occurred at South Lakkhankhola at Bandar upazila in Narayanganj on Wednesday. The dead is Sabuj Mia, 38. The injured are Liton, 32, Firoz Mia, 32, Abdul Jalil, 32, and Tara Mia, 26. Harun-Or-rashid, OC of the Bandar Police Station told bdnews24.com that a few days ago the roof of Hasina Begum's building had been laid. But it collapsed when they were dismantling the bamboo and wood support. Sabuj died on the spot. The fire brigade team recovered the body after trying for two hours, the police officer said. One of the injured was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital and the other three were admitted to Narayanganj Sadr Hospital. Ahsanul Kabir, the deputy assistant director of Narayanganj Fire Service and Civil Defence told journalists that the roof collapsed due to faulty construction. bd
